<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id90037356-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2736d–1"><num value="2736d–1">§ 2736d–1.</num><heading> Donald M. Payne International Development Fellowship Program</heading><subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id90037357-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2736d–1/a"><num value="a" class="bold">(a)</num><heading class="bold"> Authorization</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">There shall be in the Department a Donald M. Payne International Development Fellowship Program.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id90037358-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2736d–1/b"><num value="b" class="bold">(b)</num><heading class="bold"> Purpose</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The program required by subsection (a) shall continue to provide financial assistance, mentoring, and professional development opportunities to individuals pursuing careers in international development.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<subsection style="-uslm-lc:I19" class="indent2 firstIndent-2" id="id90037359-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6" identifier="/us/usc/t22/s2736d–1/c"><num value="c" class="bold">(c)</num><heading class="bold"> Administration</heading><content><p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The program required by subsection (a) shall be administered by the Department, consistent with existing law and regulations.</p>
</content>
</subsection>
<sourceCredit id="id9003735a-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">(<ref href="/us/pl/119/60/dE/tI/s5136">Pub. L. 119–60, div. E, title I, § 5136</ref>, <date date="2025-12-18">Dec. 18, 2025</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/139/1568">139 Stat. 1568</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id9003735b-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="id9003735c-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I87" topic="definitions" id="id9003735d-2930-11f1-8918-be39dde81dc6">
<heading class="centered smallCaps">Definition</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">For definition of “Department” as used in this section, see <ref href="/us/pl/119/60/s5002">section 5002 of Pub. L. 119–60</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t22/s2651">section 2651 of this title</ref>.</p>
</note>
</notes>
